radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated measuring up to 14 mm and is air and fluid filled with extensive surrounding fat stranding. An appendicolith is noted in the body of the appendix. Mild thickening of the proximal ascending colon/cecum. No extraluminal air or drainable fluid collection. The visualized lung bases are clear. There is no pericardial or pleural effusion. The gallbladder is normal and without gallstones, but mild gallbladder wall edema is noted.
